<task id="095" project="spaarkeai-compose-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Extend IInvokePlaybookAi with document-context overload (userContext + Document)</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completed>2026-07-01</completed>
    <estimated-effort>1.5 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>bff-api, facade, adr-013, public-contracts, ai-platform</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <dependencies>094</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <phase>8-streaming-sse-backend</phase>
    <supplement-spec>spec-supplement-2026-07-01-three-pane-pivot.md FR-S4</supplement-spec>
    <adr-amendment>ADR-013 refined facade contract widened — see task 102</adr-amendment>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Extend the `IInvokePlaybookAi` facade with an overload that accepts
    document-context arguments. The existing parameter-only signature
    (used by M365 Copilot Agent) MUST continue to work — new args are
    optional.

    New signature (added to `IInvokePlaybookAi.cs`):

      Task&lt;PlaybookInvocationResult&gt; InvokePlaybookAsync(
          Guid playbookId,
          IReadOnlyDictionary&lt;string, string&gt;? parameters,
          string? userContext,                        // NEW: extracted document text
          DocumentContext? document,                  // NEW: structured metadata
          PlaybookInvocationContext context,
          CancellationToken cancellationToken = default);

    OR extend the existing method with optional args (whichever fits the
    interface's current C# 8 nullable / OverloadResolution rules).

    Do NOT remove the old signature; both must resolve.

    Rationale (for ADR-013 amendment task 102):
      The refined facade was designed for parameter-only invocations
      (M365 Copilot Agent — the only pre-Compose consumer). Document-
      context invocation is a legitimate use case that a facade extension
      handles cleanly. Bypassing the facade to use
      IPlaybookOrchestrationService directly (Compose's alternative)
      would violate ADR-013's CRUD/AI boundary. This extension is a
      Path B ADR-013 amendment per CLAUDE.md §6.5.

    Update PlaybookInvocationResult if needed (probably not — existing
    shape suffices).

    Verify:
      1. `dotnet build` succeeds
      2. `IInvokePlaybookAi` still callable via the old 4-arg shape
      3. Interface tests updated (add mock/stub coverage for new overload)
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Facade contract engineer with ADR-013 refinement literacy. Understands
    the CRUD/AI boundary and why the extension is warranted (not a
    boundary breach).
  </role>

  <goal>
    IInvokePlaybookAi has a document-context overload. Existing callers
    are unaffected. Ready for task 096 (impl updates) and task 097
    (endpoint SSE conversion).
  </goal>

