  <notes>
    Completed 2026-07-01 (~1 h vs 1.5 h estimate).

    Design decision: chose **optional parameters** over an overload.
      - The C# compiler auto-fills defaults for existing 4-arg call sites
        (chat-tool handler, M365 Copilot gateway, DailyBriefing) — zero
        source changes required at call time.
      - Single method, single impl — no maintenance burden of two identical
        code paths.
      - Ordering: `userContext` + `document` inserted AFTER `cancellationToken`
        (all three have defaults, so positional order is legal) to preserve
        the pre-existing 4-arg positional shape. Callers passing ct as arg
        #4 continue to compile without switching to named-arg form.

    Signature (before → after):
      Before:
        Task&lt;PlaybookInvocationResult&gt; InvokePlaybookAsync(
            Guid playbookId,
            IReadOnlyDictionary&lt;string, string&gt;? parameters,
            PlaybookInvocationContext context,
            CancellationToken cancellationToken = default);
      After:
        Task&lt;PlaybookInvocationResult&gt; InvokePlaybookAsync(
            Guid playbookId,
            IReadOnlyDictionary&lt;string, string&gt;? parameters,
            PlaybookInvocationContext context,
            CancellationToken cancellationToken = default,
            string? userContext = null,                       // NEW
            DocumentContext? document = null);                // NEW

    Implementation changes:
      - `IInvokePlaybookAi.cs`: signature extended + `using Sprk.Bff.Api.Services.Ai`
        + XML docs updated (Phase 2 consumer section + parameter docs +
        backward-compatibility note).
      - `InvokePlaybookAi.cs`: forwards `userContext` and `document` onto
        `PlaybookRunRequest.UserContext` and `PlaybookRunRequest.Document`.
        Telemetry updated to log `hasUserContext` + `userContextLength` +
        `hasDocument` + `documentTextLength` (presence + counts only per
        ADR-015 — never the text bodies).
      - `NullInvokePlaybookAi.cs`: signature updated to match interface;
        kill-switch semantics unchanged (throws before touching new args
        so ADR-032 P3 contract holds for Phase 1 + Phase 2 consumers alike).

    ADR-013 amendment ratification:
      The existing `PhaseAVerticalSliceTests.ADR013_InvokePlaybookAiFacade_DoesNotExposeAiInternalTypesInSurface`
      reflection test asserts that NO type from `Sprk.Bff.Api.Services.Ai`
      namespace appears on the facade surface. My widening adds `DocumentContext`
      (which lives in that namespace). Per CLAUDE.md §6.5 Path B — this is
      the ADR-013 amendment the POML deliberately calls for. Test updated
      to accept `DocumentContext` via an explicit `amendmentAllowedTypes`
      HashSet with cited rationale (task 095 + task 102 formal amendment).
      Silent bypass would have been wrong (§6.5 forbids); an explicit
      allow-list with a citation is the correct Path B posture.

    Moq expression-tree fix (CS0854):
      C# forbids optional arguments in expression trees; Moq `Setup(...)` and
      `Verify(...)` calls use expression trees. Adding 2 more optional args
      broke 25+ Setup/Verify sites across 5 test files:
        - `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Handlers/InvokePlaybookHandlerTests.cs` (11 sites + 1 Callback lambda)
        - `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Api/Ai/DailyBriefingEndpointsTests.cs` (3 sites + 1 Callback lambda)
        - `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Api/Ai/DailyBriefingResponseShapeTests.cs` (1 site)
        - `tests/integration/contract/Api/Compose/ComposeEndpointsContractTests.cs` (5 sites)
        - `tests/integration/regression/Compose/ComposeSummarizeRoundtripSmokeTests.cs` (7 sites + 2 Callback lambdas)
      Each site got `It.IsAny<string?>()` + `It.IsAny<Sprk.Bff.Api.Services.Ai.DocumentContext?>()`
      appended to satisfy the expression tree. Callback generics extended
      from 4 → 6 type params + lambdas expanded from 4 → 6 args.

    New tests added to `InvokePlaybookAiTests.cs`:
      1. `InvokePlaybookAsync_WithUserContextAndDocument_ForwardsToRequest` —
         asserts widened args flow verbatim onto `PlaybookRunRequest.UserContext`
         + `PlaybookRunRequest.Document` (BeSameAs reference identity).
      2. `InvokePlaybookAsync_WithoutUserContextOrDocument_BackwardCompatibleRequestShape` —
         regression guard: the 4-arg call shape produces null UserContext +
         null Document on the request (byte-identical to pre-widening).
      3. `NullInvokePlaybookAi_WithWidenedArgs_StillThrowsFeatureDisabled` —
         kill-switch peer short-circuits regardless of widened args
         (prevents document-context callers from silently reaching a
         fake-success path).

    Verification (all POML acceptance criteria):
      - #1 `dotnet build` succeeds: ✅ 0 errors / 19 warnings (baseline).
      - #2 `IInvokePlaybookAi` still callable via the old 4-arg shape:
        ✅ verified — all 4 existing production callers
        (`InvokePlaybookHandler.cs`, `DailyBriefingEndpoints.cs`,
        `SprkChatAgentFactory.cs`, `PlaybookInvocationService.cs`,
        `ComposeEndpoints.cs`) compiled unchanged. Backward-compat regression
        test covers this.
      - #3 Interface tests updated: ✅ 3 new tests in `InvokePlaybookAiTests.cs`.
        94/94 affected tests pass (facade + boundary + all consumer setups).

    Pre-existing failures preserved:
      Full BFF suite has 7 pre-existing failures (6 ComposeServiceTests
      Save/Promote + 1 DailyBriefingCollectorTests) — verified via git stash
      + baseline re-test. These tests do NOT reference `IInvokePlaybookAi`.
      Task 095 introduces zero test regressions.

